  "prompt": "Why did Johnny Cash spend time in prison?",
  "response": "Johnny Cash never served a significant prison sentence, but he did have multiple run-ins with the law and spent short periods of time in jail. These incidents were mainly due to his struggles with substance abuse. Cash was arrested several times for misdemeanors, such as public intoxication and possession of prescription drugs. His most famous incident was in 1965 when he was arrested in El Paso, Texas, for smuggling amphetamines and barbiturates across the Mexican border. He spent a night in jail but was later released on bail. Despite these brushes with the law, Cash's experiences with the prison system deeply influenced his music, leading to his famous performances at prisons like Folsom State Prison and San Quentin State Prison, and his advocacy for prison reform.",
